Leishmaniasis, visceral, fatal - Brazil (Sao Paulo)
990616225510
Date: Thu, 22 Jul 1999 13:25:45 -0300
From: Carlos Brisola Marcondes <cbrisola@mbox1.ufsc.br>
Source: Folha de SÃ£o Paulo 22 Jul 1999

A 2-year-old girl died of visceral leishmaniasis in Aracatuba, Sao
Paulo, being the second death due to this disease in the state in
history.
--
Carlos Brisola Marcondes
Depto Microb. Paras./CCB
UFSC- Campus Trindade
88040-900 Florianopolis (SC)
Brazil
<cbrisola@mbox1.ufsc.br>
[We hope this diagnosis will raise the level of awareness of
physicians in the state to the occurrence of this disease, and
prevent further deaths. Once diagnosed, the disease can be
treated with antimonials, amphotericin B or pentamidine.
Untreated, it is usually fatal - Mod.JW
